[3] Fiji
Date: 7 Mar 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Radio New Zealand International, Wellington, 3 Mar 2004 [edited]
<http://www.rnzi.com/index.php>

Northern Fiji on dengue fever "red alert"
-------------------------------------
Health authorities in Fiji have declared an alert following 2
confirmed cases of dengue fever in the Northern Division. Commercial
radio station Legend says a Health Ministry spokesperson has
confirmed that 2 patients suffering from dengue were admitted to
Labasa hospital. The patients have stabilized through a successful
management programme.
The spokesman says the red alert has been issued for the Northern
Division and other parts of the country because of the dengue
outbreak in Indonesia, which [carries a high fatality rate] and seems
to have spread to Fiji. He says there is a high risk of dengue
because of a high mosquito population during the current rainy season.
Previous outbreaks of dengue in Fiji have resulted in tens of
thousands becoming sick and scores of deaths.
--
